1
00:00:04,743 --> 00:00:06,852
<i>You jeopardized a man's life.</i>

2
00:00:06,876 --> 00:00:08,506
Am I gonna get fired?

3
00:00:08,530 --> 00:00:10,247
I don't know if I'll be allowed
to practice medicine again.

4
00:00:10,271 --> 00:00:11,639
It's not up to me.

5
00:00:11,663 --> 00:00:12,989
You're supposed to
be her supervisor.

6
00:00:13,013 --> 00:00:15,904
That never should have happened.

7
00:00:15,928 --> 00:00:17,210
- Get out of my house!
- Daniel!

8
00:00:17,234 --> 00:00:19,038
Why are you speaking
this way to my brother?

9
00:00:19,062 --> 00:00:21,084
Because your brother
is suing Ripley

10
00:00:21,108 --> 00:00:23,129
<i>and the hospital
for malpractice.</i>

11
00:00:23,153 --> 00:00:26,393
I didn't think it
would happen so fast.

12
00:00:26,417 --> 00:00:29,135
<i>Alzheimer's is just a
very tricky diagnosis.</i>

13
00:00:29,159 --> 00:00:31,659
I'm sorry about this afternoon.

14
00:00:31,683 --> 00:00:35,054
I didn't have the bandwidth
for worlds colliding.

15
00:00:35,078 --> 00:00:36,490
Of course not.

16
00:00:36,514 --> 00:00:38,168
<i>It wasn't the time or the place.</i>

17
00:00:41,171 --> 00:00:43,671
- Thank you.
- Mm-hmm. You too.

18
00:00:43,695 --> 00:00:46,674
Medium black coffee for
me, and I got her today.

19
00:00:46,698 --> 00:00:47,719
What are you doing?

20
00:00:47,743 --> 00:00:49,895
Because it's her birthday.

21
00:00:49,919 --> 00:00:50,896
Oh, happy birthday.

22
00:00:50,920 --> 00:00:52,550
Thank you.

23
00:00:52,574 --> 00:00:54,987
I gotta say, I'm so pumped
for the big bash tonight.

24
00:00:55,011 --> 00:00:56,510
I mean, pretty cool.

25
00:00:56,534 --> 00:00:57,816
You have the same birthday
as your grandbaby?

26
00:00:57,840 --> 00:00:59,296
I mean, come on.

27
00:00:59,320 --> 00:01:00,819
Well, here's hoping
that my birthday twin

28
00:01:00,843 --> 00:01:03,213
doesn't pass out before cake.

29
00:01:03,237 --> 00:01:05,737
So is tonight really
the first night

30
00:01:05,761 --> 00:01:07,652
that Bert and the kids
are meeting Dennis?

31
00:01:07,676 --> 00:01:09,001
Well, just two of them.

32
00:01:09,025 --> 00:01:12,744
David was gonna fly in,
but work got too hectic.

33
00:01:12,768 --> 00:01:14,137
So how are you feeling?

34
00:01:14,161 --> 00:01:16,704
Introducing the
boyfriend to the family.

35
00:01:16,728 --> 00:01:19,925
Well, let's just say I only
got about three hours of sleep

36
00:01:19,949 --> 00:01:21,535
last night, so...
- Oh, come on.

37
00:01:21,559 --> 00:01:24,016
Dennis is gonna charm
their socks off.

38
00:01:24,040 --> 00:01:25,452
Yeah, well, I better get going.

39
00:01:25,476 --> 00:01:27,976
I got a meeting on the
Pawel suit in five.

40
00:01:28,000 --> 00:01:29,891
Sharon, I'm so sorry you
gotta deal with that crap.

41
00:01:29,915 --> 00:01:31,067
No worries.

42
00:01:31,091 --> 00:01:33,243
How are things at home?

43
00:01:33,267 --> 00:01:36,115
Honestly, it's a
little strained.

44
00:01:36,139 --> 00:01:38,204
Yeah, I can imagine.

45
00:01:38,228 --> 00:01:40,076
So let me know how
the meeting goes?

46
00:01:40,100 --> 00:01:41,599
- Will do.
- All right.

47
00:01:41,623 --> 00:01:43,862
Happy birthday.
- Thank you.

48
00:01:43,886 --> 00:01:45,037
- That's right.
- Okay.

49
00:01:45,061 --> 00:01:46,212
All right, so
these are my girls.

50
00:01:46,236 --> 00:01:47,561
That is Melissa. That's Alice.

51
00:01:47,585 --> 00:01:51,217
And Melissa is 24,
and Alice is 26?

52
00:01:51,241 --> 00:01:52,808
- Yes, good memory.
- Oh.

53
00:01:54,114 --> 00:01:55,178
And where are they?

54
00:01:55,202 --> 00:01:56,875
That's Playa Del Carmen.

55
00:01:56,899 --> 00:01:59,225
Melissa was actually supposed
to go with her girlfriend,

56
00:01:59,249 --> 00:02:00,400
but the girlfriend
broke up with her

57
00:02:00,424 --> 00:02:02,185
the night before the trip.

58
00:02:02,209 --> 00:02:04,143
- Oh, poor kid.
- Mm-hmm.

59
00:02:04,167 --> 00:02:05,449
I almost canceled my whole week

60
00:02:05,473 --> 00:02:07,146
and hopped on the
next flight to Mexico.

61
00:02:07,170 --> 00:02:09,453
You are a good mom.

62
00:02:09,477 --> 00:02:13,239
Well, my girls mean
everything to me.

63
00:02:13,263 --> 00:02:15,285
Isn't it just awful
watching your kids

64
00:02:15,309 --> 00:02:17,156
go through their
first heartbreak?

65
00:02:17,180 --> 00:02:19,419
Do you remember Sean's?

66
00:02:19,443 --> 00:02:21,117
Sean's first serious breakup?

67
00:02:21,141 --> 00:02:23,771
- Yes.
- Yeah.

68
00:02:23,795 --> 00:02:27,819
Uh, well, actually,
Sean was the one doing

69
00:02:27,843 --> 00:02:30,517
the heartbreaking back then.

70
00:02:30,541 --> 00:02:32,674
Yeah, that does line up.

71
00:02:35,459 --> 00:02:37,872
No one doubts the
suit is merit less,

72
00:02:37,896 --> 00:02:40,614
but given the nature
of the injury...

73
00:02:40,638 --> 00:02:43,617
It's gonna be your
word against Pawel's.

74
00:02:43,641 --> 00:02:46,446
The bottom line is that
juries are unpredictable,

75
00:02:46,470 --> 00:02:48,492
not to mention that
it could end up

76
00:02:48,516 --> 00:02:50,885
costing the hospital
more to defend the claim

77
00:02:50,909 --> 00:02:52,409
than to just settle it.

78
00:02:52,433 --> 00:02:55,325
So trust me, the cost-benefit
analysis is clear.

79
00:02:55,349 --> 00:02:56,611
It's to settle.

80
00:03:03,226 --> 00:03:04,638
Sorry, I gotta get
back to the ED.

81
00:03:04,662 --> 00:03:06,510
We got two helicopters inbound.
- Of course.

82
00:03:06,534 --> 00:03:07,772
Listen, I'll draft
the settlement.

83
00:03:07,796 --> 00:03:09,165
I'll get it over
to Pawel's lawyer.

84
00:03:09,189 --> 00:03:10,296
And then there'll
be some documents

85
00:03:10,320 --> 00:03:11,384
I'll need you to
sign, Dr. Ripley.

86
00:03:11,408 --> 00:03:12,864
Now, hold on a second.

87
00:03:12,888 --> 00:03:16,998
Listen, Dr. Ripley, this is
ultimately your decision.

88
00:03:17,022 --> 00:03:20,306
If you wanna fight the suit,
the hospital will defend you.

89
00:03:20,330 --> 00:03:22,656
- Reluctantly.
- Vigorously.

90
00:03:22,680 --> 00:03:24,615
- Can I think it over?
- Absolutely.

91
00:03:24,639 --> 00:03:26,759
- What's there to think about?
- That's not a problem.

92
00:03:28,730 --> 00:03:30,316
Take the day.

93
00:03:30,340 --> 00:03:31,733
Thank you, Ms. Goodwin.

94
00:03:34,562 --> 00:03:37,758
Sharon, we are
settling this case.

95
00:03:37,782 --> 00:03:42,198
Oh, hey, I hear the renegade
resident Dr. Ahmad got canned.

96
00:03:42,222 --> 00:03:43,677
That true?

97
00:03:43,701 --> 00:03:46,332
Try not to look so broken
up about it, okay, Peter?

98
00:03:46,356 --> 00:03:48,160
And no, she was not canned.

99
00:03:48,184 --> 00:03:52,623
She's suspended pending an
investigation of the incident.

100
00:03:55,844 --> 00:03:57,691
Shayna Ellis,
28-year-old female.

101
00:03:57,715 --> 00:03:59,867
She and a companion were
driving a UTV on the freeway

102
00:03:59,891 --> 00:04:01,042
and got rear-ended.

103
00:04:01,066 --> 00:04:02,305
Took a side-by-side
on the freeway?

104
00:04:02,329 --> 00:04:03,871
Shocking it didn't
end well, right?

105
00:04:03,895 --> 00:04:05,351
She was pretty
combative at the scene,

106
00:04:05,375 --> 00:04:06,570
wouldn't let us treat her.

107
00:04:06,594 --> 00:04:09,225
Gave her two of Versed,
four of morphine.

108
00:04:09,249 --> 00:04:11,120
She's sedated but rousable.

109
00:04:12,556 --> 00:04:14,882
Shayna, can you hear me?
You're at Chicago Med.

110
00:04:14,906 --> 00:04:16,884
We're gonna take good
care of you, okay?

111
00:04:16,908 --> 00:04:18,538
It's a good thing she was
wearing her seat belt.

112
00:04:18,562 --> 00:04:19,713
The driver was not.

113
00:04:19,737 --> 00:04:20,888
She got ejected
from the vehicle.

114
00:04:20,912 --> 00:04:22,044
Yikes.

115
00:04:24,438 --> 00:04:26,546
Clear breath sounds bilaterally.

116
00:04:26,570 --> 00:04:27,591
She's tachycardic.

117
00:04:27,615 --> 00:04:28,809
I'm gonna ultrasound.

118
00:04:28,833 --> 00:04:30,550
Cycle her blood pressure cuff.
- Mm-hmm.

119
00:04:30,574 --> 00:04:31,638
Dr. Ripley, I'm
bringing a second victim

120
00:04:31,662 --> 00:04:32,900
into Baghdad right now.

121
00:04:32,924 --> 00:04:34,230
- Zach.
- On it.

122
00:04:38,452 --> 00:04:40,560
BP 150/100.

123
00:04:40,584 --> 00:04:42,301
I'm not seeing any free fluid.

124
00:04:42,325 --> 00:04:43,694
No.

125
00:04:43,718 --> 00:04:45,086
Her right kidney look a
little abnormal to you?

126
00:04:45,110 --> 00:04:46,566
Yeah, it does.

127
00:04:46,590 --> 00:04:48,133
Nancy, let's get chest
and pelvis X-rays,

128
00:04:48,157 --> 00:04:49,265
as well as an abdominal CT.

129
00:04:49,289 --> 00:04:51,136
Yep. On it.

130
00:04:51,160 --> 00:04:52,877
We did everything we could
for her at the scene,

131
00:04:52,901 --> 00:04:54,748
but I don't know if
she's gonna make it.

132
00:04:54,772 --> 00:04:56,576
Like her friend here, she
wasn't wearing a helmet.

133
00:04:56,600 --> 00:04:58,820
- Get back!
- What's going on?

134
00:05:02,606 --> 00:05:03,931
- Hey!
- I see them!

135
00:05:03,955 --> 00:05:05,411
There they are! Look!

136
00:05:05,435 --> 00:05:06,760
Back off right now!

137
00:05:06,784 --> 00:05:08,196
They do not consent
to treatment!

138
00:05:08,220 --> 00:05:10,220
We're taking them out of here!
- Like hell you are!

139
00:05:14,401 --> 00:05:16,533
Get your hands off her!

140
00:05:23,801 --> 00:05:24,736
You good?

141
00:05:24,760 --> 00:05:25,890
Yeah.

142
00:05:29,416 --> 00:05:30,784
Ow.

143
00:05:30,808 --> 00:05:33,439
Maggie, who the hell
are these people?

144
00:05:33,463 --> 00:05:37,467
Apparently, they're
members of a cult.

145
00:05:50,611 --> 00:05:52,328
They've all been removed?

146
00:05:52,352 --> 00:05:53,372
Yep, and we've
got extra security

147
00:05:53,396 --> 00:05:54,808
posted outside in
case any of them

148
00:05:54,832 --> 00:05:55,809
try to get back in.

149
00:05:55,833 --> 00:05:57,898
Thanks, Kev.

150
00:05:57,922 --> 00:06:00,205
What did you find
out about them?

151
00:06:00,229 --> 00:06:03,077
Well, they call themselves
HTS, Heal Thyself.

152
00:06:03,101 --> 00:06:06,342
The woman was driving
the UTV, Dakota Andrews.

153
00:06:06,366 --> 00:06:09,170
AKA Cea, short for
Panacea, is the leader.

154
00:06:09,194 --> 00:06:10,737
But wasn't Panacea
some kind of God?

155
00:06:10,761 --> 00:06:11,912
The Greek goddess of healing.

156
00:06:11,936 --> 00:06:13,087
She carried with her a potion

157
00:06:13,111 --> 00:06:14,591
that could cure any
illness or injury.

158
00:06:16,550 --> 00:06:18,484
I minored in
classical mythology.

159
00:06:18,508 --> 00:06:19,443
Mm-hmm.

160
00:06:19,467 --> 00:06:21,095
They're deeply anti-government.

161
00:06:21,119 --> 00:06:23,446
They believe the medical
industrial complex

162
00:06:23,470 --> 00:06:25,491
is a tool used to
control society,

163
00:06:25,515 --> 00:06:28,189
that big pharma is incentivized
by the federal government

164
00:06:28,213 --> 00:06:30,583
to actually keep people sick.

165
00:06:30,607 --> 00:06:33,238
It appears to be mostly
an online community,

166
00:06:33,262 --> 00:06:36,197
but the top brass live together
on a commune in Indiana.

167
00:06:36,221 --> 00:06:38,199
Yeah, we picked them up
right along the border.

168
00:06:38,223 --> 00:06:40,201
And how did they all
get here so fast?

169
00:06:40,225 --> 00:06:41,681
Well, Shayna called
someone from the scene

170
00:06:41,705 --> 00:06:43,117
before we sedated her.

171
00:06:43,141 --> 00:06:44,205
We had to circle the
choppers a couple times

172
00:06:44,229 --> 00:06:45,492
because of strong winds.

173
00:06:47,102 --> 00:06:48,688
Shayna's labs just posted.

174
00:06:48,712 --> 00:06:50,995
She's coming down from CT now,
and then I'll send Dakota up.

175
00:06:51,019 --> 00:06:52,257
Great. Thanks, Zach.

176
00:06:52,281 --> 00:06:54,912
Excuse me.
- Yeah.

177
00:06:54,936 --> 00:06:56,783
Well, I guess I'll
be hitting the road,

178
00:06:56,807 --> 00:06:57,915
unless you wanna put me to work.

179
00:06:57,939 --> 00:07:00,091
Coming off a night
shift. I'm free.

180
00:07:00,115 --> 00:07:02,485
I appreciate how much
you've helped us,

181
00:07:02,509 --> 00:07:04,443
but you've been way too
generous with your time.

182
00:07:04,467 --> 00:07:06,227
Why don't you go home
and get some sleep?

183
00:07:06,251 --> 00:07:08,055
You know, I may have an
ulterior motive why I've been

184
00:07:08,079 --> 00:07:09,622
hanging around the ED so much.

185
00:07:09,646 --> 00:07:10,928
Oh, yeah? What's that?

186
00:07:10,952 --> 00:07:12,538
Oh.

187
00:07:12,562 --> 00:07:13,583
So sorry.

188
00:07:13,607 --> 00:07:14,584
Trisha, are you okay?

189
00:07:14,608 --> 00:07:17,238
No, I'm good.

190
00:07:17,262 --> 00:07:18,370
See you around, Mags.

191
00:07:18,394 --> 00:07:19,482
Yeah.

192
00:07:23,007 --> 00:07:24,202
Are you two...

193
00:07:24,226 --> 00:07:26,509
Oh, no. We're just friends.

194
00:07:26,533 --> 00:07:29,860
In that case, you mind
putting in a good word for me?

195
00:07:29,884 --> 00:07:31,339
I think I got a little crush.

196
00:07:31,363 --> 00:07:33,820
Oh, yeah. I'd be happy to.

197
00:07:33,844 --> 00:07:35,387
Thank you, Maggie.

198
00:07:35,411 --> 00:07:36,586
You're the best.

199
00:07:41,852 --> 00:07:43,743
Oh, Daniel, good.

200
00:07:43,767 --> 00:07:46,093
Thank you for meeting me.

201
00:07:46,117 --> 00:07:47,268
What's going on?

202
00:07:47,292 --> 00:07:49,140
Will you give this to Sharon?

203
00:07:49,164 --> 00:07:50,620
I'm afraid I'm not
going to be able

204
00:07:50,644 --> 00:07:52,099
to make the party after all.

205
00:07:52,123 --> 00:07:55,363
Oh, bummer. What's... what's up?

206
00:07:55,387 --> 00:07:57,694
Pawel, he needs my help.

207
00:07:58,739 --> 00:08:01,457
Well, what does he... what
does he need your help with?

208
00:08:01,481 --> 00:08:05,354
Grocery shopping, a
few other errands.

209
00:08:06,573 --> 00:08:08,072
Daniel, please.
- I didn't say anything.

210
00:08:08,096 --> 00:08:09,030
I did not say anything.

211
00:08:09,054 --> 00:08:10,553
He can't drive.

212
00:08:10,577 --> 00:08:12,816
I am not going to have
him walk to the store.

213
00:08:12,840 --> 00:08:14,339
He's my brother.

214
00:08:14,363 --> 00:08:16,363
Sweetie, do you really
believe that he can't drive?

215
00:08:18,628 --> 00:08:21,955
Dr. Ripley, I'm sure, did
not mean to harm Pawel.

216
00:08:21,979 --> 00:08:23,348
But mistakes happen.

217
00:08:23,372 --> 00:08:25,742
Dr. Ripley didn't make
a mistake, Liliana.

218
00:08:25,766 --> 00:08:27,657
You were in the room.
You were right there.

219
00:08:27,681 --> 00:08:29,093
I have to go to him.

220
00:08:29,117 --> 00:08:31,530
I really do not want
to continue this.

221
00:08:31,554 --> 00:08:34,296
But if we must, at home.

222
00:08:36,037 --> 00:08:37,560
Okay.

223
00:08:44,959 --> 00:08:46,240
Shayna.

224
00:08:46,264 --> 00:08:48,808
Shayna, hi. I'm Dr. Ripley.

225
00:08:48,832 --> 00:08:50,506
Cea.

226
00:08:50,530 --> 00:08:51,724
Where is Cea?

227
00:08:51,748 --> 00:08:54,205
You and your companion
were in an accident.

228
00:08:54,229 --> 00:08:57,164
Where is she? Where
did you take her?

229
00:08:57,188 --> 00:08:58,731
Your friend is in
critical condition,

230
00:08:58,755 --> 00:09:00,733
but we're doing everything
we can to help her.

231
00:09:00,757 --> 00:09:02,213
She doesn't need your help.

232
00:09:02,237 --> 00:09:03,649
I beg to differ,

233
00:09:03,673 --> 00:09:06,957
but right now, we
need to focus on you.

234
00:09:06,981 --> 00:09:08,045
What is this?

235
00:09:08,069 --> 00:09:09,786
What are you putting inside me?

236
00:09:09,810 --> 00:09:11,657
It's just some medication to
control your blood pressure.

237
00:09:11,681 --> 00:09:14,834
- I want it out. Now.
- I wouldn't advise that.

238
00:09:14,858 --> 00:09:19,535
Shayna, your CT revealed a
mass on your adrenal gland.

239
00:09:19,559 --> 00:09:21,754
It's likely a pheochromocytoma.

240
00:09:21,778 --> 00:09:23,713
It's a rare tumor that
releases epinephrine

241
00:09:23,737 --> 00:09:26,367
into your bloodstream, causing
the blood pressure to spike.

242
00:09:26,391 --> 00:09:28,369
Have you found
yourself experiencing

243
00:09:28,393 --> 00:09:30,371
panic attack-like
symptoms lately?

244
00:09:30,395 --> 00:09:32,833
Rapid heartbeat, shortness of
breath, that kind of thing?

245
00:09:35,705 --> 00:09:37,161
Okay, well, this appears

246
00:09:37,185 --> 00:09:38,771
to have gone untreated
for some time.

247
00:09:38,795 --> 00:09:41,339
Where is the adrenal gland?

248
00:09:41,363 --> 00:09:42,558
We have two of them.

249
00:09:42,582 --> 00:09:45,082
They're located on
top of your kidneys.

250
00:09:45,106 --> 00:09:48,738
The crash caused you to
bleed in and around the mass,

251
00:09:48,762 --> 00:09:50,478
which makes it even
more imperative

252
00:09:50,502 --> 00:09:53,090
that we surgically remove
the pheo as soon as possible

253
00:09:53,114 --> 00:09:54,874
to prevent life-threatening
complications

254
00:09:54,898 --> 00:09:56,073
like heart attack and stroke.

255
00:10:01,383 --> 00:10:04,057
I appreciate your
time and your concern

256
00:10:04,081 --> 00:10:06,190
for my well-being, Doctor...

