299
00:11:40,438 --> 00:11:41,807
Lungs are equal bilaterally.

300
00:11:41,831 --> 00:11:43,679
Put your hands by
your side for me.

301
00:11:43,703 --> 00:11:44,984
There you go.

302
00:11:45,008 --> 00:11:47,160
Pelvis is loose.

303
00:11:47,184 --> 00:11:48,509
Let's get X-ray in here.

304
00:11:48,533 --> 00:11:50,381
Let's get a binder on
him in the meantime.

305
00:11:50,405 --> 00:11:51,817
Why don't we wait
for X-ray to confirm?

306
00:11:51,841 --> 00:11:54,646
Because I know a busted
pelvis when I feel one.

307
00:11:54,670 --> 00:11:57,127
Dr. Marcel, the ICU just called.

308
00:11:57,151 --> 00:11:58,868
Carson Miller's labs are back.

309
00:11:58,892 --> 00:12:00,913
Okay, one second.
I'll be right there.

310
00:12:00,937 --> 00:12:02,852
I can bind a pelvis
without supervision.

311
00:12:06,638 --> 00:12:09,835
All right. I'll be back.

312
00:12:09,859 --> 00:12:11,426
What is his deal today?

313
00:12:19,260 --> 00:12:20,716
Hey.

314
00:12:20,740 --> 00:12:22,239
Hi, you.

315
00:12:22,263 --> 00:12:25,372
I just wanted to apologize
again for the other night.

316
00:12:25,396 --> 00:12:28,288
Oh, my gosh, you have
to stop apologizing.

317
00:12:28,312 --> 00:12:29,899
I get it.

318
00:12:29,923 --> 00:12:33,424
You'd just been served. I'd
need a night to myself too.

319
00:12:33,448 --> 00:12:36,407
Speaking of, what's going
on with the lawsuit?

320
00:12:38,322 --> 00:12:40,431
I think we're gonna settle.

321
00:12:40,455 --> 00:12:42,172
You seem thrilled.

322
00:12:42,196 --> 00:12:45,523
Yeah, I've just never been
one to walk away from a fight.

323
00:12:45,547 --> 00:12:47,351
Doesn't feel great.
- Mm-hmm.

324
00:12:47,375 --> 00:12:51,398
Especially considering this
is the dude who messed up our,

325
00:12:51,422 --> 00:12:54,488
you know, tea,

326
00:12:54,512 --> 00:12:57,230
which I was really looking
forward to, by the way.

327
00:12:57,254 --> 00:12:59,798
As was I.

328
00:12:59,822 --> 00:13:00,823
Rain check?

329
00:13:02,607 --> 00:13:05,349
I think we can make that happen.

330
00:13:11,312 --> 00:13:13,290
I see we had the same idea

331
00:13:13,314 --> 00:13:15,292
combating the mid-morning slump.

332
00:13:15,316 --> 00:13:17,163
I'm trying to, but
the pickings are slim.

333
00:13:17,187 --> 00:13:18,232
Ugh.

334
00:13:21,409 --> 00:13:23,343
Isn't that Sam Abrams' wife?

335
00:13:23,367 --> 00:13:25,389
Yeah, it is.

336
00:13:25,413 --> 00:13:26,694
Trini, why don't you
get a treatment room

337
00:13:26,718 --> 00:13:28,087
with a crib ready?
- Got it.

338
00:13:28,111 --> 00:13:29,436
Michelle, hey.

339
00:13:29,460 --> 00:13:32,613
- Oh, Hannah, thank God.
- Hey. What's going on?

340
00:13:32,637 --> 00:13:33,919
Mason had a fall.

341
00:13:33,943 --> 00:13:35,268
I've never heard
him cry like this.

342
00:13:35,292 --> 00:13:36,574
He won't stop.
- Okay.

343
00:13:36,598 --> 00:13:37,793
I'm scared something's
really wrong.

344
00:13:37,817 --> 00:13:39,011
Yeah, okay. Let's
get him checked out.

345
00:13:39,035 --> 00:13:40,341
Come on.
- Okay.

346
00:13:46,042 --> 00:13:48,064
So how'd this happen?

347
00:13:48,088 --> 00:13:50,153
He was in his stroller
seat, and he just fell out.

348
00:13:50,177 --> 00:13:51,719
He wasn't buckled in?

349
00:13:51,743 --> 00:13:53,112
I had just unbuckled him.

350
00:13:53,136 --> 00:13:54,810
How far was the
drop, would you say?

351
00:13:54,834 --> 00:13:56,463
About two, three feet?

352
00:13:56,487 --> 00:13:57,551
Yeah.

353
00:13:57,575 --> 00:13:59,858
Yeah, exactly. Not very far.

354
00:13:59,882 --> 00:14:04,254
Well, he seems to be a little
fussy when I move his left arm.

355
00:14:04,278 --> 00:14:05,733
He's clearly favoring his right.

356
00:14:05,757 --> 00:14:07,474
I'd like to get an X-ray.

357
00:14:07,498 --> 00:14:09,563
Is that safe for
a baby of his age,

358
00:14:09,587 --> 00:14:10,695
the radiation exposure?

359
00:14:10,719 --> 00:14:12,697
Absolutely. The
radiation is minute.

360
00:14:12,721 --> 00:14:15,134
Michelle, I was in surgery.

361
00:14:15,158 --> 00:14:16,135
I just got your text.

362
00:14:16,159 --> 00:14:18,746
- Honey.
- Okay.

363
00:14:18,770 --> 00:14:20,879
All right.

364
00:14:20,903 --> 00:14:22,663
Did he lose consciousness?

365
00:14:22,687 --> 00:14:24,274
Has he been crying
appropriately the whole time?

366
00:14:24,298 --> 00:14:25,623
- Mm-hmm.
- Did he vomit at all?

367
00:14:25,647 --> 00:14:26,842
Is he taking his bottle?

368
00:14:26,866 --> 00:14:28,191
Sam, you can take a deep breath.

369
00:14:28,215 --> 00:14:29,583
We're not seeing
any cause for alarm.

370
00:14:29,607 --> 00:14:31,716
Yeah, Hannah's right.
He's awake and alert.

371
00:14:31,740 --> 00:14:34,850
He was crying, but he's
consolable now, obviously.

372
00:14:34,874 --> 00:14:36,963
And Mason's gonna be just fine.

373
00:14:44,361 --> 00:14:45,904
How much Levophed is he on?

374
00:14:45,928 --> 00:14:47,863
- Five mics.
- Okay.

375
00:14:47,887 --> 00:14:49,386
Keep titrating him down.

376
00:14:49,410 --> 00:14:51,586
He's doing a good job
clearing his sepsis.

377
00:14:53,196 --> 00:14:56,001
It's the perfect window
to transplant him.

378
00:14:56,025 --> 00:14:57,655
It's gonna close.

379
00:14:57,679 --> 00:14:59,831
Just a matter of time
before he gets sick again.

380
00:14:59,855 --> 00:15:02,529
I have to imagine he's top on
the transplant list, right?

381
00:15:02,553 --> 00:15:05,271
Hopefully a pair of lungs
will come through soon.

382
00:15:05,295 --> 00:15:06,707
Yeah.

383
00:15:06,731 --> 00:15:09,449
Their founder, a woman
named Dakota Andrews,

384
00:15:09,473 --> 00:15:12,539
claims that all illness is a
manifestation of stored trauma.

385
00:15:12,563 --> 00:15:15,238
Hmm. Not a completely
baseless idea.

386
00:15:15,262 --> 00:15:18,197
We do know that excess
adrenaline, cortisol,

387
00:15:18,221 --> 00:15:19,677
can cause all kinds
of health issues.

388
00:15:19,701 --> 00:15:22,549
Agreed, except that
her proposed remedy

389
00:15:22,573 --> 00:15:24,987
is a combination of
energy work, meditation,

390
00:15:25,011 --> 00:15:27,337
and herbal teas she
makes containing.

391
00:15:27,361 --> 00:15:29,687
God knows what... no
medicine, no surgery,

392
00:15:29,711 --> 00:15:31,558
no diagnostic tests.

393
00:15:31,582 --> 00:15:34,170
How did she start to
attract a following?

394
00:15:34,194 --> 00:15:35,214
After she claimed to have cured

395
00:15:35,238 --> 00:15:37,086
her own malignant meningioma.

396
00:15:37,110 --> 00:15:38,826
Started going by
the name Panacea

397
00:15:38,850 --> 00:15:40,959
and posting her ideas online.

398
00:15:40,983 --> 00:15:42,221
Happy to have a
chat with Shayna,

399
00:15:42,245 --> 00:15:43,831
but needless to say,
just because she has

400
00:15:43,855 --> 00:15:45,659
a belief system at odds
with our treatment plan...

401
00:15:45,683 --> 00:15:47,096
No, I know.

402
00:15:47,120 --> 00:15:51,143
I don't think she lacks
decisional capacity.

403
00:15:51,167 --> 00:15:53,450
And even if she does,
she's been heavily coached

404
00:15:53,474 --> 00:15:55,060
to pass the test.

405
00:15:55,084 --> 00:15:56,148
I was actually
hoping you might know

406
00:15:56,172 --> 00:15:58,890
something about deprogramming.

407
00:15:58,914 --> 00:16:01,197
What?
- Well, just, you know,

408
00:16:01,221 --> 00:16:03,025
in practice, historically
speaking, anyway,

409
00:16:03,049 --> 00:16:04,548
pretty horrifying tactic.

410
00:16:04,572 --> 00:16:06,158
Usually starts off
with kidnapping,

411
00:16:06,182 --> 00:16:07,725
and then there's
illegal imprisonment.

412
00:16:07,749 --> 00:16:10,423
Yeah, no, I wasn't
suggesting we kidnap her.

413
00:16:10,447 --> 00:16:12,382
Look, getting
somebody to abandon

414
00:16:12,406 --> 00:16:14,253
a deeply held belief system

415
00:16:14,277 --> 00:16:15,820
is not typically a
one-and-done idea,

416
00:16:15,844 --> 00:16:16,908
but let me see where she's at.

417
00:16:16,932 --> 00:16:18,151
Appreciate it.

418
00:16:21,067 --> 00:16:24,568
The results of Dakota
Andrews' head CT.

419
00:16:24,592 --> 00:16:27,614
Subdural hematoma with
brainstem herniation.

420
00:16:27,638 --> 00:16:29,921
Neurosurgery saw her,
said her exam is congruent

421
00:16:29,945 --> 00:16:32,837
with brain death and supported
by the confirmatory testing.

422
00:16:32,861 --> 00:16:34,056
They just moved her to the ICU.

423
00:16:34,080 --> 00:16:35,709
Any family to notify?

424
00:16:35,733 --> 00:16:37,581
An older brother
who lives in Ohio.

425
00:16:37,605 --> 00:16:38,974
He's on his way
here to say goodbye,

426
00:16:38,998 --> 00:16:41,280
and he's expressed a desire

427
00:16:41,304 --> 00:16:43,500
to possibly donate
his sister's organs.

428
00:16:43,524 --> 00:16:46,329
Hey, uh... sorry.

429
00:16:46,353 --> 00:16:48,070
Y'all mind keeping me
posted if the family decides

430
00:16:48,094 --> 00:16:49,897
to go with organ donation?

431
00:16:49,921 --> 00:16:52,988
I've got a patient up in the
ICU in dire need of new lungs.

432
00:16:53,012 --> 00:16:54,163
- Sure thing.
- Yeah. Of course.

433
00:16:54,187 --> 00:16:56,730
Great, thank you.

434
00:16:56,754 --> 00:16:58,210
Hey, Zach?

435
00:16:58,234 --> 00:17:00,821
Let me see Dakota's
head CT again.

436
00:17:00,845 --> 00:17:02,630
I just wanna look at something.

437
00:17:10,899 --> 00:17:13,008
They're ready.

438
00:17:13,032 --> 00:17:14,835
Hey. What's going on?

439
00:17:14,859 --> 00:17:17,229
We're heading up to
interventional radiology

440
00:17:17,253 --> 00:17:19,188
to angio his pelvis.
- FAST was negative?

441
00:17:19,212 --> 00:17:20,798
Have you been transfusing him?

442
00:17:20,822 --> 00:17:21,973
Obviously.

443
00:17:21,997 --> 00:17:23,496
BP 90 systolic.

444
00:17:23,520 --> 00:17:24,715
His pressure's dropped before.

445
00:17:24,739 --> 00:17:26,064
We just need to
give him more blood.

446
00:17:26,088 --> 00:17:28,066
No, change of plans.

447
00:17:28,090 --> 00:17:29,589
We're taking him up to the OR.

448
00:17:29,613 --> 00:17:31,156
We'll pack his pelvis,
get him resuscitated,

