00:17:31,180 --> 00:17:32,679
then we can go to IR.

450
00:17:32,703 --> 00:17:33,811
I'll call upstairs.

451
00:17:33,835 --> 00:17:36,553
Isn't the OR an
unnecessary delay?

452
00:17:36,577 --> 00:17:38,685
Mr. Acosta's been responding
well to blood and plasma.

453
00:17:38,709 --> 00:17:40,644
Let's continue to
resuscitate him in IR.

454
00:17:40,668 --> 00:17:42,689
You don't wanna take an
unstable patient to IR.

455
00:17:42,713 --> 00:17:44,735
Things start going south,
you're much better off

456
00:17:44,759 --> 00:17:45,693
being in the operating room.

457
00:17:45,717 --> 00:17:47,129
Trust me.

458
00:17:47,153 --> 00:17:48,347
Good judgment comes
from experience.

459
00:17:48,371 --> 00:17:49,783
Experience comes
from bad judgment.

460
00:17:49,807 --> 00:17:53,091
You should put that
on a bumper sticker.

461
00:17:53,115 --> 00:17:54,421
Let's go.

