473
00:18:22,753 --> 00:18:24,122
What are you saying?

474
00:18:24,146 --> 00:18:27,256
These types of fractures,
especially in babies,

475
00:18:27,280 --> 00:18:31,042
typically come from
direct blunt-force trauma.

476
00:18:31,066 --> 00:18:32,348
What?

477
00:18:32,372 --> 00:18:34,069
We should loop in Ms. Goodwin.

478
00:18:40,771 --> 00:18:43,185
Hospital policy, not
to mention the law,

479
00:18:43,209 --> 00:18:47,014
mandates that we notify
DCFS in these situations.

480
00:18:47,038 --> 00:18:49,104
But this is Sam and Michelle.

481
00:18:49,128 --> 00:18:51,932
There's just... there's no
way that this is child abuse.

482
00:18:51,956 --> 00:18:54,109
You can't say that with
100% certainty, Hannah.

483
00:18:54,133 --> 00:18:56,981
None of us were there.
- And if we turn a blind eye

484
00:18:57,005 --> 00:18:58,896
because it's
Dr. Abram's family...

485
00:18:58,920 --> 00:19:00,202
Look, I know how it looks.

486
00:19:00,226 --> 00:19:02,029
It looks like
preferential treatment

487
00:19:02,053 --> 00:19:04,858
because he's the
chief of neurosurgery.

488
00:19:04,882 --> 00:19:06,860
And frankly, that's
exactly what it would be.

489
00:19:06,884 --> 00:19:09,385
We all know how quickly
these investigations

490
00:19:09,409 --> 00:19:10,603
can go off the rails.

491
00:19:10,627 --> 00:19:12,692
They could lose their baby.
- I agree.

492
00:19:12,716 --> 00:19:16,522
It seems highly implausible
that Mrs. Abrams

493
00:19:16,546 --> 00:19:18,785
did something
intentional to Mason.

494
00:19:18,809 --> 00:19:22,180
But she is also
a sleep-deprived,

495
00:19:22,204 --> 00:19:23,747
terrified new mother.

496
00:19:23,771 --> 00:19:26,837
We have no idea what's
going on in her head.

497
00:19:26,861 --> 00:19:30,362
We have to err on
the side of caution.

498
00:19:30,386 --> 00:19:32,669
Look, if you'd like,
I'll speak to the Abrams.

499
00:19:32,693 --> 00:19:34,497
No, no, no. It
should come from us.

500
00:19:34,521 --> 00:19:36,107
We'll talk to them.

501
00:19:36,131 --> 00:19:37,872
Thank you.

502
00:19:45,662 --> 00:19:47,249
Went about as well
as I expected,

503
00:19:47,273 --> 00:19:48,902
so, you know, not great.

504
00:19:48,926 --> 00:19:51,122
I mean, she thinks that Dakota
is this omnipotent being,

505
00:19:51,146 --> 00:19:52,819
and everything she
says is the truth,

506
00:19:52,843 --> 00:19:55,909
and everything else is a lie.

507
00:19:55,933 --> 00:20:00,697
Well, I think I might have
a way to break the spell,

508
00:20:00,721 --> 00:20:02,220
prove to her that Dakota isn't

509
00:20:02,244 --> 00:20:04,353
an all-powerful celestial being.

510
00:20:04,377 --> 00:20:06,485
She didn't cure her
malignant meningioma

511
00:20:06,509 --> 00:20:07,747
with meditation and herbs.

512
00:20:07,771 --> 00:20:09,575
She never had brain cancer.

513
00:20:09,599 --> 00:20:11,229
You see Dakota's
